race.comment: MY ZEPHYR (5) improved sharply winning over 1107m at Geelong two-and-a-half weeks ago. Peaks for this and Egan goes on. Only has to hold the form to go close. This is a step up, but this looks well within her grasp. THE KILL CLUB (8) is on a quick back-up and with weight relief can build on the 56 win at Ararat. Races forward and gives herself every chance. COLOUR OUR WORLD (9) resumes and has placed 2/3 fresh. He's right up to this and has jumped out well. Yendall continues his association with the mare. THAILESS (1) was beaten just 2L   in city class last time and this suits. Will be handy despite the tricky draw and also deserves plenty of consideration. STORMBENDER (10) resumes and looks ready to go. Lightly raced and was last seen on the synthetic leading and winning on debut, heavily bet. Has the upside.
